30
00:03:29,761 --> 00:03:31,442
[SPEAKER_02]: The UN is not there.

31
00:03:33,199 --> 00:03:43,984
[SPEAKER_02]: the UN is absent from the managing or the resolution of any of the conflicts I have just mentioned.

32
00:03:45,024 --> 00:03:46,025
[SPEAKER_02]: And it needn't be so.

33
00:03:47,185 --> 00:03:47,865
[SPEAKER_02]: It needn't be so.

34
00:03:49,706 --> 00:03:55,949
[SPEAKER_02]: Some say the United Nations has to play a role in this thing.

35
00:03:57,158 --> 00:04:01,500
[SPEAKER_02]: Well, it's not going to happen unless we do things differently.

36
00:04:01,900 --> 00:04:08,303
[SPEAKER_02]: It's not going to happen because we believe in that or there's a principle about that.

37
00:04:08,843 --> 00:04:25,910
[SPEAKER_02]: It is only going to happen when there is a conviction in leaders in belligerent nations that the participation of the United Nations, and in particular the Secretary General, is going to

38
00:04:27,402 --> 00:04:32,343
[SPEAKER_02]: facilitate a better outcome than what they are currently having.

39
00:04:33,744 --> 00:04:39,806
[SPEAKER_02]: And this conviction grew in me because of my own experience.

40
00:04:40,686 --> 00:04:47,828
[SPEAKER_02]: It's not an idea that I had or some words that I tried to put nicely on a piece of paper in the vision.

41
00:04:48,548 --> 00:04:54,050
